	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real person — maybe you. The empty side of the bed. The questions from people who don't know what to say. The fear of co-parenting, of money, of holidays, of who you are now. The quiet shame when church culture feels more like a courtroom than a home. The grief that comes in waves you can't predict.</p><p>None of this means you are unloved or beyond hope. It means you are human, walking through one of the deepest losses a person can know. There is a Father who stays close to the brokenhearted — not to judge you, but to bind up your wounds. He has something to say about who you still are to Him.</p>`}
