	aFatherHeading={`A Father for those walking through divorce`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what almost no one tells you in the middle of a divorce: the answer to this grief isn't getting your old life back, proving you were right, or finally feeling like you're not a failure. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father who stays close to the brokenhearted and never breaks His covenant with you.</p><p>You were not made to carry this alone, and you were never meant to earn your way back into love. The One who made you doesn't hand you a scarlet letter or measure your worth by what broke. He calls you His beloved child — not the married you, not the fixed-up you, but <em>you</em>, right now, in the middle of the loss.</p><p>So before you're an ex, a single parent, a cautionary tale in someone's story — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady presence in the empty house, the voice that says: I see your grief, I am near, and I will never leave you or divorce your heart.</p>`}
