	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel healed the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's love isn't a quick fix for grief — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father binding up something the heartbreak tried to tear apart.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I see the grief you carry — the rejection, the failure you keep replaying, the nights the house is too quiet. And I want you to hear Me over all of it: a covenant may have been broken, but Mine with you is not. You are still My beloved, and I have not turned My face from you.</p><p>You don't have to earn your way back to Me or prove you're worth loving again. I am close to the brokenhearted, and I am close to you. I will bind up your wounds, I will make a way where you see none, and I will never leave you nor divorce your heart. Come to Me weary — you don't have to be strong first. I'm your Father, I am near, and I am holding you still."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for those walking through divorce`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we come to You on behalf of every person walking through separation and divorce — carrying grief, rejection, and a fear of the future no one fully sees. You are close to the brokenhearted, so draw near to them now. Let them feel Your nearness in the lonely hours and Your comfort where the wound is deepest.</p><p>Heal what has been torn. Bind up every wound, quiet the shame, and silence the lie that they are condemned or beyond Your love. Where there is fear about money, co-parenting, or starting over, be their provider and their peace. Guard and surround any children in the middle of this loss, and let them know they are held by a Father who never leaves.</p><p>Father, make a way in the wilderness for them — do a new thing they cannot yet see. Steady them, strengthen them, and remind them every single day that even when a covenant breaks, Your covenant of love does not. Let them know You as their true home, their Redeemer, and their never-failing Father.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
