	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for divorce and heartbreak?`, answer: `Psalm 34:18 (the Father is close to the brokenhearted), Psalm 147:3 (He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds), Isaiah 41:10 (do not fear, I am with you), Deuteronomy 31:6 (He will never leave you nor forsake you), Isaiah 43:18-19 (I am doing a new thing), Matthew 11:28 (come to Me, weary ones, and find rest), and Jeremiah 29:11 (plans for a future and a hope) all speak straight to the grief of divorce. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say to someone going through a divorce?`, answer: `Scripture meets you in the grief rather than condemning you. Psalm 34:18 promises God is close to the brokenhearted, and Psalm 147:3 says He heals the brokenhearted and binds up their wounds. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a Father who stays near in the loss — read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
